/* Header-style frosted blur. The header itself uses pure
   `background: transparent + blur(12px)`, but it sits over varied
   page content so the blur is visible. The buy-bar sits over the
   mostly-uniform cream wash near the page bottom, so a pure
   backdrop blur produces no visible diffusion. To get a clearly
   frosted-glass look here we layer:
     - A faint translucent white wash so the surface is always visible
     - The same `blur(12px)` backdrop filter
     - `saturate(180%)` (the iOS recipe) — saturates whatever IS behind,
       so any color variation in the backdrop reads vividly through it. */
border: 1.5px solid rgba(229, 232, 235, 0.5);
border-radius: 18px;
background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(180%);
-webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(180%);
